Package com.redis.foundation.data

Class DataGrid

java.lang.Object
com.redis.foundation.data.DataGrid
public class DataGrid extends Object
A DataGrid manages a collection of columns and rows of data items. The grid is typically instantiated and populated with rows of data, but was not designed for the selective updating, inserting and deletion of rows. These features may be added in the future.

      • The goal of the DataGrid is to strike a balance between providing enough properties to adequately model application related data without overloading it.
      • This method offers a mechanism to capture additional (application specific) properties that may be needed.
      • Properties added with this method are transient and will not be stored when saved or cloned.
      Parameters:
      aName - Property name (duplicates are not supported).
      anObject - Instance of an object.
